title: TODO Why does the definition of Functor use 0, while Monad's doesn't?
pid: e75b4508-e55f-45b5-a660-351e836674ae
body: |2-
  https://idris2.readthedocs.io/en/latest/tutorial/interfaces.html#functors-and-applicatives
  interface                  Functor (0 f : Type -> Type) where
    map  : (m : a -> b) -> f a -> f b
  interface Applicative m => Monad   (m   : Type -> Type) where
   (>>=) : m a -> (a -> m b) -> m b
